Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.64,0:00:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A case where building blocks are the clues! Heiji's\Nand Uncle's deductions conflict! Which one will win?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.15,0:00:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.65,0:00:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the body of a child and the brains of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.36,0:00:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.86,0:02:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, Detective Samonji series, file 44. "The Last\NWill and Testament Prepared by a Devil," final chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.87,0:02:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.08,0:02:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew you'd come by to buy one,\Nlittle boy, so I kept one especially for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Than you, Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.67,0:02:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh boy, oh boy! I'm so into this series.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.68,0:02:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, I'll eat dinner quickly and\Nfinish reading this before I go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.77,0:02:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when I get up tomorrow I'll read\Nit a second time. It will be just as fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.78,0:02:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.82,0:02:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome home!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.53,0:02:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one's deduction show\N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.33,0:02:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.05,0:02:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, so the little brat is finally home.\NLet's go out and eat some good food now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.22,0:03:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, it's still early! We can go\Nsomewhere that's slightly further away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.81,0:03:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what do you want to eat? Just name it, little guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.56,0:03:08.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.40,0:03:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pass? Pasta? Ah, Italian food, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.48,0:03:16.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, I heard that a stylish\Npasta restaurant opened up in Haido city.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.91,0:03:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, let's go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.57,0:03:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Haido City is close enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.04,0:03:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right-then, it's decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.08,0:03:25.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.58,0:03:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so full!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.38,0:03:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having genuine spaghetti once\Nin a while is really not that bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.05,0:03:36.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right! Coming here\Nwas definitely the right choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.76,0:03:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was so delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.34,0:03:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what are you guys doing here?\NKazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.43,0:03:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This dark-skinned guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.31,0:03:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold it, what's with that attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.31,0:03:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Showing up without making an appointment...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.40,0:03:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already had plans of my own, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.36,0:04:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, plans. That's why we came\Nall this way, to discuss your schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.54,0:04:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Schedule?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.16,0:04:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! We wanted to invite Ran and you guys over\Nagain. There are still lots of great places in Osaka to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.50,0:04:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great places in Osaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.67,0:04:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.55,0:04:17.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Osaka's trademark...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.35,0:04:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K-Koushien?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takarazuka?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.26,0:04:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K-Koushien?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.35,0:04:24.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takarazuka?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.70,0:04:31.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Translator's Note: Koushien is the famous baseball field near\NKobe, Japan, known for hosting the Japanese high school baseball finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.10,0:04:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't those both in Hyogo prefecture?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.56,0:04:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't aware of any plans to go to Koushien.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.15,0:04:34.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Translator's Note: The Takarazuka Review, based in Takarazuka, Japan, is\Na group of all woman theater troupes known for their lavish performances.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.15,0:04:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takarazuka is a bolt from the blue for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.78,0:04:38.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I already tell you? The auntie\Nwho lives nearby promised us tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.28,0:04:42.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you say it, you did\Nmumble something like that once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.70,0:04:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, why can't we go to both places?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:51.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good idea! I just wanted to take\Neveryone one to see the high school baseball finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.50,0:04:55.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drats, then we can't go to both.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.59,0:04:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.47,0:05:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me that auntie is one of those five.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.22,0:05:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're a group of ladies in our\Nneighborhood famous for loving Takarazuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.94,0:05:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They save up money for a whole year and\Nuse it during the summer vacation period
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.07,0:05:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To go and see Takarazuka continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.78,0:05:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there is one day they\Ncouldn't use their dearly bought tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.33,0:05:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Co-Could that day be...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.70,0:05:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Koushien finals?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.50,0:05:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you see, president of the company\Nwhere those five aunties work loves high school baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.80,0:05:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every year, for the finals, he takes all\Nthe employees of the company to go watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.88,0:05:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they promised to give me\Nthe Takarazuka tickets for that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.01,0:05:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now, since the Koushien finals\Nwere rained out on their original date,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.35,0:05:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They couldn't know which day the\Nfinals would be when the were buying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.19,0:05:52.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I guess there's no choice. This\Ntime, Kazuha, you'll have to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.86,0:05:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can go see the same Takarazuka show any time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.78,0:06:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the summer finals at Koushien is a\Nfierce competition that only happens once a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.33,0:06:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying! They show high school\Nbaseball on the news and sports specials all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.83,0:06:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! Baseball has to be watched in person!\NWhat's the point in seeing the results on the news?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.88,0:06:15.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takarazuka is always best live!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.76,0:06:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These Takarazuka tickets for such great seats\Nthat normal people would never be able to get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.47,0:06:25.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. You want to go see Takarazuka too, right'?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.85,0:06:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.89,0:06:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey kid, if you're a guy, it's baseball, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.90,0:06:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.86,0:06:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about you, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.11,0:06:40.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see. This time I'd definitely go for the\Nrefreshing hot-blooded environment of Koushien.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.99,0:06:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then again, the gorgeous passionate\Nenvironment of Takarazuka wouldn't be bad either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.99,0:06:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.75,0:06:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about this: We'll go to the place\Nchosen by whoever wins a deduction competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.96,0:06:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deduction?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.17,0:06:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Competition?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.76,0:07:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wednesday last month I was told there\Nwas a murder at the office of some company.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.76,0:07:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems there were some unusual issues, so\NInspector Megure asked me to lend him my wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.89,0:07:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The company is actually in this area. I was\Ngoing to drop by after dinner to take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.19,0:07:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, I don't like using a murder case as the subject of\Na bet, but it seems the criminal hasn't yet been caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.95,0:07:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's in order to solve a case, I don't think it's a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.79,0:07:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it, Kazuha? Shall we have a competition?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.96,0:07:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's so sneaky! How can I beat\NHeiji at a deduction competition?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.21,0:07:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s side will\Nbe supported by me, Sleeping Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.68,0:07:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? Thank you, Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.93,0:07:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's nothing. Sleeping Kogorou has\Nalways been a friend of the underdog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.48,0:07:54.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already seen through your\Nweakly-disguised ruse, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.69,0:07:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, will you help me too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.86,0:07:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, let's work hard for Takarazuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.61,0:08:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How sneaky, finding two people to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.83,0:08:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, I guess there's no other\Nchoice. I'll have to deal with this four-eyes kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.42,0:08:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sneakiest one is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.50,0:08:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.75,0:08:17.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to trouble you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.51,0:08:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.84,0:08:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, inside is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.76,0:08:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop blocking the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.26,0:08:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.68,0:08:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you can't just waltz into a crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.14,0:08:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it. Forensics has\Nalready completely investigated the scene, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.23,0:08:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder victim was the president of this toy\Nmanufacturing company, Tsugiya Kenshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 53 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.11,0:08:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This appears to be both the\Npresident's home and the toy factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.99,0:08:49.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The presumed time of death is\NSunday, June 29th, at around 5 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.87,0:08:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was found the next day,\NMonday the 30th, around 10 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.46,0:08:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who found him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:09:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was found by four employees of this company.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.51,0:09:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four employees?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, those four always go just before\Nwork to eat breakfast together at that coffee shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.90,0:09:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, that's why there were four people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.73,0:09:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so those four people discovered the president\Ntied up with ropes and beaten to death with a golf club.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.61,0:09:24.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you tell, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.16,0:09:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See how the ink has mostly\Nbeen spilled near the victim's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.29,0:09:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably the criminal and the\Npresident were struggling with each other
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.96,0:09:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And spilled the ink that was on top of the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.84,0:09:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he tied the president up in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when the ink adhering to\Nthe ropes left marks all over the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.14,0:09:45.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That proves the president was\Nstill struggling when he was tied up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.22,0:09:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, then how about the\Nevidence that he was killed by a golf club?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.14,0:09:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are blood stains only near the head and\Naround the head are several 10 cm long, narrow stains.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.86,0:10:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are marks from an iron golf club.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.86,0:10:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These were made when the criminal\Nrepeatedly struck the head of the fallen man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.95,0:10:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did he bother to hit\Nhim after he'd already tied him up?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.58,0:10:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must've been asking him the number to the\Nsafe. Look, the door of that safe has been left open.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.76,0:10:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, the criminal must have\Nbeen an outsider looking for valuables.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.59,0:10:25.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We still don't know if it was an outsider or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.51,0:10:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, after the criminal tied up the\Npresident and got the number to the safe out of him,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He beat the man who had seen his face to\Ndeath with a golf club. This point is indisputable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.98,0:10:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Inspector'?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.78,0:10:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.74,0:10:43.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Father, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.28,0:10:46.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So far, those two have been taking the foreground!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.78,0:10:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Up until now, these are all things that 'even the police\Ncan determine by just looking at the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.46,0:10:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Even the police..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.90,0:10:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:10:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't there anything else? What was so unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.96,0:11:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.88,0:11:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.80,0:11:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These were found near the president's corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These four building blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.60,0:11:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Building blocks? There's\Nplenty scattered around the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, for some reason only these four have\Nthe president's fingerprints and ink stains.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.66,0:11:25.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ink?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.24,0:11:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and if you line up the faces\Nwith ink stains and finger prints,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.80,0:11:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.47,0:11:46.64,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Translator's Note: (Omocha) = toys
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.47,0:11:46.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toys?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.86,0:12:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.36,0:12:02.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Translator's Note: (omochi-ya) = rice cake store
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.36,0:12:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, wait, could it be a rice cake store?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.95,0:12:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be a rice cake store.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.49,0:12:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right, there seem to be\Nblocks with small 'tsu' and 'ya' on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.79,0:12:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you show me the spot where\Nthe four pieces in this picture were laying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, this picture was taken when the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.22,0:12:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, this person is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.59,0:12:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is Tsujiya, the murdered\Npresident of this toy manufacturing company.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.60,0:12:35.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These four blocks were mixed in with\Nthe pile of blocks to the president's left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.70,0:12:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as for why only the four with 'o-mo-chi-ya' on\Nthem had the president's fingerprints and ink stains...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.24,0:12:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ink stains must have come from the ink bottle\Non the desk which spilled onto the president's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.58,0:12:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question is, who put the\Nink onto the building blocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.84,0:13:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we might also consider that the\Npresident's fingerprints on the blocks,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.72,0:13:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might have been left when the criminal\Nforced the murdered president to hold the blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.85,0:13:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.51,0:13:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were the president's fingerprints\Nreally left on only those four blocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.94,0:13:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah. The other blocks piled\Nthere also have the president's fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.23,0:13:23.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only these four blocks have\Nfingerprints imprinted everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.45,0:13:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not just the six faces, but\Nalso in the wells of the characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's so, then these four blocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.75,0:13:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Definitely look like a dying message left by the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.29,0:13:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? How would you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.84,0:13:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a close look at this crime scene photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.09,0:13:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president's hands were tied up behind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.30,0:13:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tied up like that; he couldn't pick\Nout the blocks except by touching them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.77,0:13:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason his fingerprints were on each of the six faces,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.40,0:14:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that he was facing backwards and\Nsearching the character wells with his fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.73,0:14:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, he touched the other blocks,\Nbut he didn't leave as many fingerprints on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.66,0:14:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each block only has characters from the same row of\Nthe syllabary so finding the right one was fairly easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.75,0:14:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so that's why only these four have ink stains.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.38,0:14:23.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, fingerprints are mostly composed\Nof sweat and oils left by the fingertips,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.63,0:14:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the sweat and oils\NI remain even after someone has died.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:32.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you make a dead person hold the blocks,\Nyou'll still get good fingerprints the first one or two times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.06,0:14:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the president picked out these four blocks behind\Nhis back while the criminal wasn't paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.28,0:14:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he rolled over to stain the chosen face with ink,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.95,0:14:50.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then rolled back and returned it to the pile of pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.37,0:14:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he didn't know when he would be\Nkilled, his hands were sweaty from fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.00,0:15:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ink stains all over the floor\Nfrom the ropes are proof of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.34,0:15:07.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this case, the president was working quickly and may\Nhave gotten the small 'yu' and the large 'yu' mixed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.22,0:15:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a toy company, so maybe the president\Nwanted to leave behind 'toy' as his dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.02,0:15:20.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's amazing! We just got here\Nand already you have all that figured out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.73,0:15:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it? Isn't it? That's what we expect from Hei...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.62,0:15:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dang it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.86,0:15:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't good, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! We\Ncan't keep getting pulled along by Heiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.99,0:15:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a competition between us and Heiji,\Nwith either Koushien or Takarazuka as the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.50,0:15:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To solve this case before Heiji, we've\Ngot to solve this 'toy' dying message first!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.96,0:15:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe one of the toys here contains a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.01,0:15:49.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, there aren't any suspicious toys here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.85,0:15:50.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.76,0:15:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, since we were also tenatively\Nconsidering those four blocks to be a dying message,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.64,0:15:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've already thoroughly inspected this office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.57,0:16:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, maybe there's another meaning to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.57,0:16:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't there many more\Ncombinations of those four characters?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.87,0:16:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Omoyachi," "ochimoya," "ochiyamo."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.75,0:16:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Oyamochi," oyachimo," "mochiyao."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.29,0:16:17.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This makes no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.34,0:16:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, did you find anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.42,0:16:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.97,0:16:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just the golf club used as the murder weapon,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.01,0:16:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a leather coat we think the criminal was wearing\Nduring the crime, stained with the president's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.40,0:16:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, both the golf club and the coat are the president's.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.02,0:16:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we can't determine who the\Ncriminal was from these two items.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.11,0:16:49.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing I don't understand is,\Nwhy did the criminal put on this coat?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.45,0:16:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blood on the left shoulder of this coat is a bit light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.99,0:16:55.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did it rub off on something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.00,0:16:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's another mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.86,0:17:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter where we searched in this office, we\Ncouldn't find a place we thought touched that blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.30,0:17:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal's hand probably\Ntouched it when he took off the coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.43,0:17:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you find the criminal's gloves or something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.39,0:17:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, speaking of blood stains,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.27,0:17:16.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a very weird looking blood stain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.52,0:17:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.27,0:17:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right here, right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.94,0:17:22.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd you crawl under there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.53,0:17:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- This blood...\N- Just a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.15,0:17:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to see if you don't look\Nclosely, but the tip of this stain looks cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.99,0:17:32.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe something was placed here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.08,0:17:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right, but what would\Nbe placed in a spot like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.33,0:17:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, the remote, the remote...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.38,0:17:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! You can't go touching things! That desk\Nhas been left-the way it was since the crime occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.93,0:18:00.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been set up for external input. In that case,\NThe thing placed here was probably a video camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for a video camera, there's\None in the president's bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.03,0:18:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, can you call forensics and have them\Ncheck to see if there're blood stains or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.53,0:18:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's odd is, if it really was a\Nvideo camera that was placed here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.83,0:18:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the criminal take it\Naway after committing the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.25,0:18:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he connected the camera and the TV together, and\Nput it here to observe president's actions while tied up,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.54,0:18:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no reason to take it away after the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.84,0:18:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.80,0:18:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's been bothering me for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.35,0:18:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.52,0:18:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems so contrived\Nsomehow. It gives me a weird feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.60,0:18:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.06,0:18:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's up, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.23,0:18:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to ask you for a little favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.19,0:18:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This deduction competition,\Ncan you let Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} win?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.82,0:18:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} was really really\Nlooking foward to going to Takarazuka with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.33,0:19:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if you hit upon anything\Nthis time, can you secretly tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, if Father hears it, it could lead him\Nto the solution to this case, just like always.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.38,0:19:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK? Please?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.30,0:19:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.31,0:19:18.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.31,0:19:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beep! Beep! Beep!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.27,0:19:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This brat is on my team.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.94,0:19:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to make a pass for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.57,0:19:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you wouldn't ditch your fellow male's\Nfriendship and run over to the girls' side, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.75,0:19:40.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Friendship? Didn't you force\Nme to be in a group with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.29,0:19:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever, I'll do anything I can to win\Nthis competition so we can go to Koushien!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.59,0:19:49.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How very frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.63,0:19:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, they matched?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.97,0:19:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With such an exceedingly small amount,\Nthe criminal probably didn't notice it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.93,0:20:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would there be a video camera here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.19,0:20:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably connected to the TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.98,0:20:07.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And used to keep an eye on the\Npresident until he gave up the number to the safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.57,0:20:10.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question is, why would he bother to do it like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.24,0:20:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he wanted to keep an eye on him, he\Ncould've just tied him up in front of the the safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.95,0:20:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the criminal put the camera to\Nthreaten that he was watching him the whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.62,0:20:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While he went into the other rooms to look for valuables.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.30,0:20:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the president was able to leave\Nbehind a dying message to identify the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.05,0:20:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, in any case, the criminal was\Nclearly very familiar with this office,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.30,0:20:37.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's also very likely the president knew him by sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.73,0:20:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leaving behind a dying message\Nindicates he knew who the killer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.65,0:20:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore the most suspicious people\Nwould be those four employees you mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.11,0:20:51.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, those four are currently with Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.16,0:20:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.78,0:20:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've obtained the alibis of the four employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.66,0:20:59.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? They all have alibis?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.79,0:21:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All four of them are designers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.40,0:21:11.30,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,400)}Aikou Nao
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.40,0:21:11.30,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,400)}Tsujiya Toy Manufacturing Account
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.14,0:21:07.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The company's chief accountant, Aikou Nao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.52,0:21:12.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,At the time of the incident around 5 PM on\NJune 29th, had left to go fishing by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.92,0:21:16.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,400)}Hasami Atsushi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.92,0:21:16.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,400)}Tsujiya Toy Manufacturing Sales
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.86,0:21:17.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The chief salesman, Hasami\NAtsushi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was at home alone enjoying videos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:20.99,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,400)}Nakagami Isao
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:20.99,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,400)}Tsujiya Toy Manufacturing Design
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.54,0:21:21.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The chief designer, Nakagami\NIsao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was at the horse racing track.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.30,0:21:25.55,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(400,400)}Iwatomi Hajime
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.00,0:21:25.55,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(400,400)}Tsujiya Toy Manufacturing Vice President
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.57,0:21:27.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The vice president, Iwatomi Hajime{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, supposedly\Nwent to go watch the final round of a gold tournament.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.07,0:21:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are all very shaky alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.49,0:21:37.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, for the time being Chiba is picking at their\Nback stories, but none of their alibis seem verifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.95,0:21:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.20,0:21:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.62,0:21:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, if it was like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.42,0:21:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the dying message contained in the blocks is...
